        "title": "feat(exec): add normalized auto mode",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Problem: OpenClaw had separate native exec approval knobs and Codex-specific Guardian config, so `auto` meant different things depending on the harness.\n- Why it matters: users need one normalized exec policy surface that maps cleanly to native OpenClaw exec and Codex app-server execution.\n- What changed: added `tools.exec.mode`, native OpenClaw auto-review plumbing for exec approval misses, and Codex app-server mapping from OpenClaw `auto` to Guardian-reviewed approvals.\n- What did NOT change (scope boundary): existing `tools.exec.security` / `tools.exec.ask` remain supported, and explicit Codex app-server policy fields still override the normalized preset.\n\n## Change Type (select all)\n\n- [ ] Bug fix\n- [x] Feature\n- [ ] Refactor required for the fix\n- [x] Docs\n- [ ] Security hardening\n- [ ] Chore/infra\n\n## Scope (select all touched areas)\n\n- [x] Gateway / orchestration\n- [x] Skills / tool execution\n- [ ] Auth / tokens\n- [ ] Memory / storage\n- [x] Integrations\n- [x] API / contracts\n- [ ] UI / DX\n- [ ] CI/CD / infra\n\n## Linked Issue/PR\n\n- Closes #\n- Related #\n- [ ] This PR fixes a bug or regression\n\n## Root Cause (if applicable)\n\nN/A.\n\n- Root cause: N/A\n- Missing detection / guardrail: N/A\n- Contributing context (if known): Native exec approval policy and Codex app-server approval policy evolved as separate configuration surfaces.\n\n## Regression Test Plan (if applicable)\n\nN/A.\n\n- Coverage level that should have caught this:\n  - [x] Unit test\n  - [x] Seam / integration test\n  - [ ] End-to-end test\n  - [ ] Existing coverage already sufficient\n- Target test or file: `src/infra/exec-approvals-policy.test.ts`, `src/agents/exec-defaults.test.ts`, `src/agents/bash-tools.exec-host-gateway.test.ts`, `extensions/codex/src/app-server/config.test.ts`, `src/gateway/sessions-patch.test.ts`\n- Scenario the test should lock in: normalized exec mode mapping, native auto-review behavior, Codex Guardian mapping, and session/directive propagation.\n- Why this is the smallest reliable guardrail: these tests cover the policy resolver, native execution seam, Codex adapter seam, and persisted session API without a full live harness.\n- Existing test that already covers this (if any): existing exec allowlist/session tests were extended.\n- If no new test is added, why not: N/A\n\n## User-visible / Behavior Changes\n\n- Adds preferred config `tools.exec.mode` with values `deny`, `allowlist`, `ask`, `auto`, and `full`.\n- Adds `/exec mode=...` directive support.\n- `tools.exec.mode=\"auto\"` enables native OpenClaw auto review for exec approval misses.\n- Codex app-server sessions map OpenClaw `auto` to Guardian-reviewed approvals when no explicit Codex app-server mode/policy overrides are set.\n\n## Diagram (if applicable)\n\n```text\nBefore:\nOpenClaw exec policy -> security/ask only\nCodex app-server -> separate guardian/yolo preset\n\nAfter:\ntools.exec.mode=auto -> native OpenClaw auto reviewer\n                     -> Codex app-server Guardian-reviewed approvals\n```\n\n## Security Impact (required)\n\n- New permissions/capabilities? (`Yes/No`) Yes\n- Secrets/tokens handling changed? (`Yes/No`) No\n- New/changed network calls? (`Yes/No`) No\n- Command/tool execution surface changed? (`Yes/No`) Yes\n- Data access scope changed? (`Yes/No`) No\n- If any `Yes`, explain risk + mitigation: `tools.exec.mode=\"auto\"` can approve low-risk read-only exec approval misses without a human prompt. The built-in reviewer fails closed to human review, avoids compound shell/mutation/network/privilege-sensitive commands, preserves legacy raw policy overrides, and Codex maps to its existing Guardian-reviewed approval posture.\n\n## Repro + Verification\n\n### Environment\n\n- OS: macOS\n- Runtime/container: Node 22 / pnpm workspace\n- Model/provider: N/A\n- Integration/channel (if any): Codex app-server harness\n- Relevant config (redacted): `tools.exec.mode=\"auto\"`\n\n### Steps\n\n1. Configure `tools.exec.mode=\"auto\"`.\n2. Resolve exec defaults or issue `/exec mode=auto`.\n3. Start a Codex app-server attempt without explicit app-server mode overrides.\n\n### Expected\n\n- Native OpenClaw exec uses auto-review semantics on approval misses.\n- Codex app-server maps the normalized OpenClaw mode to Guardian-reviewed approvals.\n\n### Actual\n\n- Verified through targeted unit/seam tests.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- [x] Failing test/log before + passing after\n- [ ] Trace/log snippets\n- [ ] Screenshot/recording\n- [ ] Perf numbers (if relevant)\n\nTargeted verification passed:\n\n```text\npnpm test src/infra/exec-approvals-policy.test.ts src/agents/exec-defaults.test.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec-host-gateway.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-exec-overrides.test.ts src/gateway/sessions-patch.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.exec-hint.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply.directive.directive-behavior.shows-current-verbose-level-verbose-has-no.test.ts\n```\n\nAlso passed:\n\n```text\npnpm config:schema:check && pnpm config:docs:check\ngit diff --check\n```\n\n`pnpm check:changed` passed conflict markers, core/extension typechecks, core/extension lint, import cycles, and auth/body guards, then the changed-test wrapper terminated `test/vitest/vitest.gateway.config.ts` after 180s with no output (`failed:143`). The touched targeted gateway test passed independently.\n\n## Human Verification (required)\n\n- Verified scenarios: exec mode normalization, config/session/directive propagation, Codex Guardian mapping, explicit override precedence, native auto-review allow/ask paths.\n- Edge cases checked: legacy lower-scope `security` / `ask` overrides beat higher-scope `mode`; explicit Codex app-server fields override normalized OpenClaw `auto`.\n- What you did **not** verify: live Codex app-server Guardian end-to-end approval flow and the full `pnpm check:changed` changed-test wrapper due the gateway shard no-output stall noted above.\n\n## Review Conversations\n\n- [x] I replied to or resolved every bot review conversation I addressed in this PR.\n- [x] I left unresolved only the conversations that still need reviewer or maintainer judgment.\n\n## Compatibility / Migration\n\n- Backward compatible? (`Yes/No`) Yes\n- Config/env changes? (`Yes/No`) Yes\n- Migration needed? (`Yes/No`) No\n- If yes, exact upgrade steps: new configs should prefer `tools.exec.mode=\"auto\"` for normalized auto-review behavior. Existing `tools.exec.security`, `tools.exec.ask`, and Codex `appServer.mode=\"guardian\"` continue to work.\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n- Risk: `auto` could be interpreted as host routing because `tools.exec.host=\"auto\"` already exists.\n  - Mitigation: docs explicitly distinguish host routing from policy mode.\n- Risk: native auto-review is too permissive.\n  - Mitigation: default reviewer only allows one-shot read-only inspection commands and asks a human for compound shell, mutation, network, inline eval, privilege-sensitive, or unparsed commands.\n- Risk: Codex-specific Guardian semantics leak into OpenClaw config.\n  - Mitigation: Codex mapping happens inside the Codex extension adapter; OpenClaw-facing config remains `tools.exec.mode=\"auto\"`.\n",
